The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Wednesday, March 10, 2004 				 ACC raises $100 m
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Mumbai, March 9: Associated Cement Companies (ACC) has raised $100 million by issuing FCCBs and GDRs to international investors to fund the acquisition of Bargarh Cement in Orissa, modernisation of another plant and other capital expenditures.																								ACC has raised $60 million through FCCBs, priced at a 35 per cent premium on Mondays closing price of Rs 277.35 on the BSE. It raised $40 million via GDRs, priced at Rs 280.05  a 1 per cent premium on Mondays closing price of Rs 277.35.																								The convertible bonds, with a maturity of five year and one day, carry a 1 per cent coupon rate. The bonds would be listed on the London Stock Exchange and ACC could exercise a call option at a conversion price of Rs 374.42 after three years. 
